The evidence with the title 'U.S. support for gay marriage edges to new high ' says May 15, 2017  ... 64 % of Americans say same-sex marriage should be legal; for the first time, majority of Protestants support gay marriage ; support for same-sex relations has also climbed , now at 72%. WASHINGTON, D.C. -- sixty-four percent of U.S. adults say same - sex marriages should be recognized by the law as valid.
